-- Databases & Relational Databases – Solutions

-- 1. A database centrally stores, organises, and protects business data so it can be reliably queried and updated by authorised users and applications.
-- 2. If a business has 100,000 customers each with multiple orders, a spreadsheet would be extremely slow, prone to formula errors, and couldn't support simultaneous updates from multiple employees.
-- 3. Separation avoids data duplication (normalisation), reduces update errors (you change a customer’s address only once), and allows independent management of each entity.